---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Story"
  description="How EduMyna emerged from real education constraints, systems failures, and a decade of running programs at scale."
>
  <Container>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto pt-16 pb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Built from constraints, not theory
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-600">
        EduMyna did not start as a startup idea. It emerged slowly from the
        realities of running education programs where scale, quality, and
        accountability actually mattered.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Video placeholder -->
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-20">
      <div class="aspect-video rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 flex items-center justify-center text-slate-500">
        Founder video goes here
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-3 text-center">
        A short, direct explanation of why EduMyna exists
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Timeline -->
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-16">
      <!-- 2013 -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-6">
        <div class="text-slate-400 font-semibold">2013</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Entering education through operations</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            The work began inside a nonprofit education ecosystem that needed to
            scale without losing intent. The problem was not content. It was
            systems, ownership, and sustainability.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Online-first -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-6">
        <div class="text-slate-400 font-semibold">Early years</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Online-first was a necessity</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            Programs had to work across geographies, time zones, and learner
            maturity levels. This forced an online-first approach long before it
            was fashionable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Platform -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-6">
        <div class="text-slate-400 font-semibold">Iteration</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">The platform followed the problems</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            The first line of code was written to remove operational bottlenecks.
            Structure, feedback loops, and progression were built to support real
            delivery, not dashboards.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Open source -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-6">
        <div class="text-slate-400 font-semibold">Open source</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Transparency over control</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            The core was made open-source to allow adaptation, scrutiny, and
            long-term trust. Self-hosting was not an afterthought. It was a
            principle.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- EduMyna -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-6">
        <div class="text-slate-400 font-semibold">Today</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">EduMyna</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            EduMyna is the consolidation of these learnings into a platform for
            people running real programs. It optimizes for clarity, iteration,
            and responsibility rather than scale-at-any-cost growth.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Container>
</Layout>